{
  "analysis": "The foreground `sleep 300; ...` polling command has not returned its diagnostic output after multiple waits. The background autotune process (PID 2918) was running and had finished writing fastText-format files when last checked. No valid `/app/model.bin` has been confirmed yet. We need to interrupt the stuck foreground poll and run a fresh combined status check to inspect the autotune log, process status, model files, and job status. Based on the result, if `/app/model.bin` exists we will verify its size and accuracy; if autotune is still running we will continue polling; if it finished without meeting constraints we will adjust the approach.",
  "plan": "Send Ctrl+C with a trailing newline to interrupt the stuck foreground poll, then run a combined diagnostic command: tail `/app/autotune.log`, check `/proc/2918`, list `/app/model*.bin`, and show `jobs`.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "C-c\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "echo '--- LOG ---'; tail -80 /app/autotune.log; echo '--- PROC ---'; if [ -d /proc/2918 ]; then echo 'PID 2918 running'; else echo 'PID 2918 done'; fi; echo '--- FILES ---'; ls -lh /app/model*.bin 2>&1; echo '--- JOBS ---'; jobs\n",
